Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Dec 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 3 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: horses grazing in communal area

Outbreak 3: Lekabi, Mahapaye, Central
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Dec 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 3 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: horses grazing in communal area

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 8 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 37.5 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering
Epidemiological comments: infection picked from routine active surveillance in 2 horses and from sick horse presenting with prepuce swelling and weight loss. Epidemiological investigations are continuing.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; traceability; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Botswana National Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Equidae / complement fixation test (CFT) / 12 Feb 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

